wwpVoiceGatewayMIB.name: wwpVoiceGatewayMIB
wwpVoiceGatewayMIB.contactinfo: Mib Meister Postal: World Wide Packets P.O. Box 950 Veradale, WA 99037 USA Phone: +1 509 242 9000 Email: mib.meister@worldwidepackets.com
wwpVoiceGatewayMIB.description: This MIB module degines the managed objects for WWP voice gateway.

wwpVoiceGatewayEndPointTable.name: wwpVoiceGatewayEndPointTable
wwpVoiceGatewayEndPointTable.description: A table of the voice gateway endpoints.

wwpVoiceGatewayEndPointEntry.name: wwpVoiceGatewayEndPointEntry
wwpVoiceGatewayEndPointEntry.description: An entry of the voice gateway endpoint.

wwpVoiceGatewayEndPointId.name: wwpVoiceGatewayEndPointId
wwpVoiceGatewayEndPointId.description: Index for the the endpoint entry.

wwpVoiceGatewayEndpoint.name: wwpVoiceGatewayEndpoint
wwpVoiceGatewayEndpoint.description: The endpoint for the voice Gateway. This object should be set to a zero length string if the Management Station wish to use the Endpoint's IP Address as the Endpoint Domain Name. Endpoint identifiers have two parts: The domain name of the gateway that is managing the endpoint. A local name within the gateway. The local name is hierarchical, for example, the local name of circuit number 13 in a multiplexed trunk that is connected to the physical interface named XYZ would be named as XYZ/13.

wwpVoiceGatewayCallAgentAddr.name: wwpVoiceGatewayCallAgentAddr
wwpVoiceGatewayCallAgentAddr.description: This object is used to configure either the domain name or the IP address of the Call Agent in standard dot notation. The complete address of a default call agent is composed of IP address/Domain Name and UDP port. wwpVoiceGatewayCallAgentAddr specifies address of the Call Agent to which RSIP(RestartInProgress) message is sent whenever system starts up or line goes up. Call agent address may be an IP address or fully qualified domain name (FQDN). This object should be set to zero length string if the Management Stations wish to attempt to obtain the CA address from a DNS server (highest priority MGCP CA is chosen).

wwpVoiceGatewayCallAgentUDPPort.name: wwpVoiceGatewayCallAgentUDPPort
wwpVoiceGatewayCallAgentUDPPort.description: This object is used to configure the UDP port of the Call Agent. The UDP port is used together with wwpVoiceGatewayCallAgentAddr to specify the destination address of the call agent to which RSIP message is sent when system starts up or line goes up.

wwpVoiceGatewayCallAgentProtocol.name: wwpVoiceGatewayCallAgentProtocol
wwpVoiceGatewayCallAgentProtocol.description: Setting this object to 'rfc2705' will enable support of RFC 2705 for this CallAgent (Only 'L' Event Package). Setting this object to 'ncs1.0' will enable support of PacketCable NCS 1.0 for the CallAgent. Setting this object to 'mgcp1Ncs1NoPackages' will enable support of Mgcp 1.0 Ncs 1.0 no event package for the CallAgent.

wwpVoiceGatewaySupportMessagePiggybackin.name: wwpVoiceGatewaySupportMessagePiggybacking
wwpVoiceGatewaySupportMessagePiggybackin.description: Setting this object to 'false' will disable message Piggybacking for this Voice Gateway.

wwpVoiceGatewayRsipKeepAliveEnable.name: wwpVoiceGatewayRsipKeepAliveEnable
wwpVoiceGatewayRsipKeepAliveEnable.description: Setting this object to 'enable' will configure the device to send periodic RSIP x-keepalive messages.

wwpVoiceGatewayRsipKeepAliveInterval.name: wwpVoiceGatewayRsipKeepAliveInterval
wwpVoiceGatewayRsipKeepAliveInterval.description: Configures the interval at which RSIP x-keepalive messages are transmitted

wwpVoiceGatewayCountryCodes.name: wwpVoiceGatewayCountryCodes
wwpVoiceGatewayCountryCodes.description: This object specifies the country for different tone and ring settings.

wwpVoiceGatewayComplexCodec.name: wwpVoiceGatewayComplexCodec
wwpVoiceGatewayComplexCodec.description: Setting this object to 'g711(0)' will only enable G711U and G711A Codec. If this object is set to 'g729(3)', then G729A and G729AB Codec will be used.

wwpVoiceGatewaySilenceSuppression.name: wwpVoiceGatewaySilenceSuppression
wwpVoiceGatewaySilenceSuppression.description: Setting this object to 'false' will disable the silence suppression for the complex codes specified by wwpVoiceGatewayComplexCodec.

wwpVoiceGatewayEchoCancellation.name: wwpVoiceGatewayEchoCancellation
wwpVoiceGatewayEchoCancellation.description: Setting this object to 'false' will disable the echo cancellation for the complex codes specified by wwpVoiceGatewayComplexCodec.

wwpVoiceGatewayPacketizationMinPeriod.name: wwpVoiceGatewayPacketizationMinPeriod
wwpVoiceGatewayPacketizationMinPeriod.description: Min packet time for the complex codes specified by wwpVoiceGatewayComplexCodec. FOR G723 the packet time is fixed to be 30ms.

wwpVoiceGatewayPacketizationMaxPeriod.name: wwpVoiceGatewayPacketizationMaxPeriod
wwpVoiceGatewayPacketizationMaxPeriod.description: Max packet time for the complex codes specified by wwpVoiceGatewayComplexCodec. FOR G723 the packet time is fixed to be 30ms.

wwpVoiceGatewayPayloadType.name: wwpVoiceGatewayPayloadType
wwpVoiceGatewayPayloadType.description: The Payload Format for the telephone events.

wwpVoiceGatewaySendEventsViaRFC2833.name: wwpVoiceGatewaySendEventsViaRFC2833
wwpVoiceGatewaySendEventsViaRFC2833.description: Setting this object to 'true' will cause the voice gateway to send Telephone Events via RFC2833 signalling using wwpVoiceGatewayPayloadType.

wwpVoiceGatewayDropVoicePktsDuringEvents.name: wwpVoiceGatewayDropVoicePktsDuringEvents
wwpVoiceGatewayDropVoicePktsDuringEvents.description: Setting this object to 'true' will cause the voice gateway to drop voice packets during RFC2833 Telephone Event packets.

wwpVoiceGatewaySquelchInbandDtmfAudio.name: wwpVoiceGatewaySquelchInbandDtmfAudio
wwpVoiceGatewaySquelchInbandDtmfAudio.description: Setting this object to 'true' will cause the voice gateway to Squelch the Inband DTMF Audio.

wwpVoiceGatewayPktsTx.name: wwpVoiceGatewayPktsTx
wwpVoiceGatewayPktsTx.description: The total number of RTP data packets transmitted by the voice gateway since starting transmission on this connection.

wwpVoiceGatewayOctetsTx.name: wwpVoiceGatewayOctetsTx
wwpVoiceGatewayOctetsTx.description: The total number of payload octets (i.e., not including header or padding) transmitted in RTP data packets by the voice gateway since starting transmission on this connection.

wwpVoiceGatewayPktsRx.name: wwpVoiceGatewayPktsRx
wwpVoiceGatewayPktsRx.description: The total number of RTP data packets received by the voice gateway since starting reception on this connection.

wwpVoiceGatewayOctetsRx.name: wwpVoiceGatewayOctetsRx
wwpVoiceGatewayOctetsRx.description: The total number of payload octets (i.e., not including header or padding) transmitted in RTP data packets by the voice gateway since starting transmission on this connection.

wwpVoiceGatewayPktsLost.name: wwpVoiceGatewayPktsLost
wwpVoiceGatewayPktsLost.description: The total number of RTP data packets that have been lost since the beginning of reception. This number is defined to be the number of packets expected less the number of packets actually received, where the number of packets received includes any which are late or duplicates.

wwpVoiceGatewayIntervalJitter.name: wwpVoiceGatewayIntervalJitter
wwpVoiceGatewayIntervalJitter.description: An estimate of the statistical variance of the RTP data packet interarrival time measured in milliseconds and expressed as an unsigned integer. The interarrival jitter J is defined to be the mean deviation (smoothed absolute value) of the difference D in packet spacing at the receiver compared to the sender for a pair of packets.

wwpVoiceGatewayLatency.name: wwpVoiceGatewayLatency
wwpVoiceGatewayLatency.description: An estimate of the network latency, expressed in milliseconds. This is the average value of the difference between the NTP timestamp indicated by the senders of the RTCP messages and the NTP timestamp of the receivers, measured when this messages are received.

wwpVoiceGatewayResetStatCounters.name: wwpVoiceGatewayResetStatCounters
wwpVoiceGatewayResetStatCounters.description: To reset voice statistic counters , this object should be set to 'reset'. A read on this object should return none(0).

wwpVoiceGatewayNumResets.name: wwpVoiceGatewayNumResets
wwpVoiceGatewayNumResets.description: This object defines the number of times that the voice gateway has been restarted.

wwpVoiceGatewayReset.name: wwpVoiceGatewayReset
wwpVoiceGatewayReset.description: Writing one of the specified values to this field causes the specified type of reboot to occur. none is the value returned when this leaf is queried. writing this value to the leaf will have no effect. reset causes the voice gateway to restart using its current configuration. resetDefault will reset the voice gateway to factory defaults.

wwpVoiceAccess.name: wwpVoiceAccess
wwpVoiceAccess.description: Setting this object to 'deny' will disable access to VMI from SMI when connected via Telnet or console.

wwpMgmtAccess.name: wwpMgmtAccess
wwpMgmtAccess.description: Setting this object to 'deny' will disable access to SMI from VMI when connected via Telnet or console.

wwpVoiceCallAgentOtaModes.name: wwpVoiceCallAgentOtaModes
wwpVoiceCallAgentOtaModes.description: Setting this object to 'ifOtaRecv' will configure the device to send OTA if and only if OTA is received from call Agent. Setting this object to 'sendOta' will configure the device to always send OTA sdp parameters.

wwpVoiceCallAgentEgressEvent.name: wwpVoiceCallAgentEgressEvent
wwpVoiceCallAgentEgressEvent.description: Setting this object to 'sendIngressEgressNotif' will configure the device to send ingress and egress fax and modem tone notification. Setting this object to 'sendIngressNotif' will configure the device to send only ingress fax and modem tone notification.

wwpVoiceCallAgentPotsLine.name: wwpVoiceCallAgentPotsLine
wwpVoiceCallAgentPotsLine.description: Setting this object to 'enable1PotLine' will configure the device to enable Line 1 only. Setting this object to 'enable2PotLine' will configure the device to enable 2 pots lines. Device 'may' require reboot to enable pot line changes.

wwpVoiceAutonomousFaxState.name: wwpVoiceAutonomousFaxState
wwpVoiceAutonomousFaxState.description: Setting this object to 'enable' will configure the device to enable autonomous fax behavior. Setting this object to 'disable' will configure the device to disable autonomous fax behavior.

wwpVoiceEndPointName.name: wwpVoiceEndPointName
wwpVoiceEndPointName.description: Setting this object will control how a voip endpoint name will be determined. This object cannot be set to 'unknown'.

wwpVoiceNotifEntCache.name: wwpVoiceNotifEntCache
wwpVoiceNotifEntCache.description: Timeout in minutes for cached DNS lookups for MGCP RQNT Notified Entity field

wwpVoiceJitterOptionState.name: wwpVoiceJitterOptionState
wwpVoiceJitterOptionState.description: Setting this object to 'enable' will configure the jitter buffer to change to an adaptive jitter buffer size. Setting this object to 'disable' will configure the jitter buffer to use a fixed jitter buffer size.

wwpVoiceJitterBufferMinPeriod.name: wwpVoiceJitterBufferMinPeriod
wwpVoiceJitterBufferMinPeriod.description: Minimum Holding time. Setting this value will limit the jitter buffer from adapting below this value. The smallest period is fixed at 20ms.

wwpVoiceJitterBufferMaxPeriod.name: wwpVoiceJitterBufferMaxPeriod
wwpVoiceJitterBufferMaxPeriod.description: Maximum Holding time. Setting this value will limit the jitter buffer from adapting above this value. The largest period is fixed at 300ms.

wwpVoiceJitterBufferTargetPeriod.name: wwpVoiceJitterBufferTargetPeriod
wwpVoiceJitterBufferTargetPeriod.description: Target Holding time. Setting this value sets the initial jitter buffer size.

wwpVoiceGatewayCodecOverride.name: wwpVoiceGatewayCodecOverride
wwpVoiceGatewayCodecOverride.description: Selecting data codec override forces the default data codec to the specified value, overriding the standard default data codec which is tied to country code. 1 = force specification of G711 PCMU as default codec 2 = force specification of G711 PCMA as default codec

wwpVoiceGatewayTestServerConnection.name: wwpVoiceGatewayTestServerConnection
wwpVoiceGatewayTestServerConnection.description: Writing one of the specified values to this field causes mesages to be sent to voice server to test connectivity

wwpVoiceGatewayLastServerResponseTime.name: wwpVoiceGatewayLastServerResponseTime
wwpVoiceGatewayLastServerResponseTime.description: Last server response timestamp. Used as part of testing voice server connectivity

wwpVoiceGatewaySipSessionTimeoutPeriod.name: wwpVoiceGatewaySipSessionTimeoutPeriod
wwpVoiceGatewaySipSessionTimeoutPeriod.description: Configures session expiration time in seconds. Set value to 0 to disable

wwpVoiceGatewaySipRegisterTimeoutPeriod.name: wwpVoiceGatewaySipRegisterTimeoutPeriod
wwpVoiceGatewaySipRegisterTimeoutPeriod.description: Configures registration expiration time in seconds. Used only when registrar is used. Set value to 0 to disable.

wwpVoiceGatewaySipForceQuotesState.name: wwpVoiceGatewaySipForceQuotesState
wwpVoiceGatewaySipForceQuotesState.description: Configuration to force display names to be embraced by double quotes.

wwpVoiceGatewaySipPhoneLineTable.name: wwpVoiceGatewaySipPhoneLineTable
wwpVoiceGatewaySipPhoneLineTable.description: SIP Pots Line table This table confures users for each POTs line

wwpVoiceGatewaySipPhoneNumber.name: wwpVoiceGatewaySipPhoneNumber
wwpVoiceGatewaySipPhoneNumber.description: Phone Number associated with this line.

wwpVoiceGatewaySipUserName.name: wwpVoiceGatewaySipUserName
wwpVoiceGatewaySipUserName.description: User Name associated with this line.

wwpVoiceGatewaySipUserDisplayName.name: wwpVoiceGatewaySipUserDisplayName
wwpVoiceGatewaySipUserDisplayName.description: User Display Name associated with this line.

wwpVoiceGatewaySipUserPassword.name: wwpVoiceGatewaySipUserPassword
wwpVoiceGatewaySipUserPassword.description: User Password associated with this line.

wwpVoiceGatewaySipDialPlan.name: wwpVoiceGatewaySipDialPlan
wwpVoiceGatewaySipDialPlan.description: Configuration for dial plan expression string. Note: subset of unix regular expressions supported.

wwpVoiceGatewaySipPhoneLineTimerTable.name: wwpVoiceGatewaySipPhoneLineTimerTable
wwpVoiceGatewaySipPhoneLineTimerTable.description: SIP Pots Line table This table configures users for each POTs line

wwpVoiceGatewaySipPhoneLineTimerEntry.name: wwpVoiceGatewaySipPhoneLineTimerEntry
wwpVoiceGatewaySipPhoneLineTimerEntry.description: Table of sip phone line configuration

wwpVoiceGatewaySipProxyAddr.name: wwpVoiceGatewaySipProxyAddr
wwpVoiceGatewaySipProxyAddr.description: The complete address of a default Proxy is composed of IP address/Domain Name and UDP port. wwpVoiceGatewayRegistrarAddr specifies address of the Proxy server to which SIP messages are sent. Proxy address may be an IP address or fully qualified domain name (FQDN).

wwpVoiceGatewaySipProxyPort.name: wwpVoiceGatewaySipProxyPort
wwpVoiceGatewaySipProxyPort.description: This object is used to configure the UDP port of the SIP Proxy Server. The UDP port is used together with wwpVoiceGatewaySipProxyAddr to specify the destination address of the Proxy to which SIP messages are sent.

wwpVoiceGatewaySipRegistrarAddr.name: wwpVoiceGatewaySipRegistrarAddr
wwpVoiceGatewaySipRegistrarAddr.description: The complete address of a default Registrar is composed of IP address/Domain Name and UDP port. wwpVoiceGatewayRegistrarAddr specifies address of the Regsitrar to which SIP Registration messages are sent whenever system starts or line goes up. Registrar address may be an IP address or fully qualified domain name (FQDN).

wwpVoiceGatewaySipRegistrarPort.name: wwpVoiceGatewaySipRegistrarPort
wwpVoiceGatewaySipRegistrarPort.description: This object is used to configure the UDP port of the SIP Registrar. The UDP port is used together with wwpVoiceGatewaySipRegistrarAddr to specify the destination addressto which SIP Registration messages are sent when system starts or line goes up.

wwpVoiceGatewaySipSyslogAddr.name: wwpVoiceGatewaySipSyslogAddr
wwpVoiceGatewaySipSyslogAddr.description: The complete address of a default SIP SysLog server is composed of IP address/Domain Name and UDP port. wwpVoiceGatewaySipSyslogAddr specifies address of the SIP SysLog server to which SIP Log messages are sent. SysLog server address may be an IP address or fully qualified domain name (FQDN).

wwpVoiceGatewaySipSyslogPort.name: wwpVoiceGatewaySipSyslogPort
wwpVoiceGatewaySipSyslogPort.description: This object is used to configure the UDP port of the SIP Log Servert. The UDP port is used together with wwpVoiceGatewaySipSyslogAddr to specify the destination address to which SIP Log mesaages are sent when system starts or line goes up.

wwpVoiceGatewaySipSyslogLogLevel.name: wwpVoiceGatewaySipSyslogLogLevel
wwpVoiceGatewaySipSyslogLogLevel.description: This object is used to configure the log level or verbosity of the SIP messages

wwpVoiceGatewaySIPDtmfEventHandling.name: wwpVoiceGatewaySIPDtmfEventHandling
wwpVoiceGatewaySIPDtmfEventHandling.description: Configuration for device to send DTMF digits via SIP INFO message or in RTP RFC2833 event message in addition to the audio tone in RTP stream. The default is always an audio tone sent in the RTP stream.

wwpVoiceGatewayHookFlashEnable.name: wwpVoiceGatewayHookFlashEnable
wwpVoiceGatewayHookFlashEnable.description: Setting this object to 'true' will configure the device to process hook flash events.. Setting this object to 'false' will configure the device to ignore hookflash events.

wwpVoiceGatewayProtocolType.name: wwpVoiceGatewayProtocolType
wwpVoiceGatewayProtocolType.description: Configuration to select VoIP protocol. Setting this value to 'mgcp' will allow the configuration the MGCP funtionality. Setting this value to 'sip' will allow the configuration the SIP funtionality

wwpVoiceGatewayProtocolEnable.name: wwpVoiceGatewayProtocolEnable
wwpVoiceGatewayProtocolEnable.description: Configuration to enable VoIP protocol. Setting this value to 'enable' will cause VoIP stack to start at bootup
